verses.text:
But his delight \add is\add* in the law of the \nd LORD\nd*;
and in his law doth he meditate day and night. 
\q1

O \nd LORD\nd* my God, if I have done this; if there be iniquity
in my hands; 
\q1

When I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, the moon
and the stars, which thou hast ordained; 
\q1

Thou madest him to have dominion over the works of thy hands;
thou hast put all \add things\add* under his feet: 
\q1

Consider \add and\add* hear me, O \nd LORD\nd* my God: lighten
mine eyes, lest I sleep the \add sleep of\add* death; 
\q1

\add O my soul\add*, thou hast said unto the \nd LORD\nd*, Thou
\add art\add* my Lord: my goodness \add extendeth\add* not to thee;
\q1

They have now compassed us in our steps: they have set their
eyes bowing down to the earth; 
\q1

The \nd LORD\nd* rewarded me according to my righteousness;
according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me. 
\q1

With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful; with an
upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright; 
\q1

The \nd LORD\nd* liveth; and blessed \add be\add* my rock;
and let the God of my salvation be exalted. 
\q1

Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice;
Selah.\f + \fr 20.3  \ft accept: Heb. turn to ashes: or, make fat\f*
\q1

Thou hast turned for me my mourning into dancing: thou hast put
off my sackcloth, and girded me with gladness; 
\q1

I will be glad and rejoice in thy mercy: for thou hast considered
my trouble; thou hast known my soul in adversities; 
\q1

Behold, the eye of the \nd LORD\nd* \add is\add* upon them that
fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy; 
\q1

Judge me, O \nd LORD\nd* my God, according to thy righteousness;
and let them not rejoice over me. 
\q1

They also that render evil for good are mine adversaries;
because I follow \add the thing that\add* good \add is\add*. 
\q1

If we have forgotten the name of our God, or stretched out
our hands to a strange god; 
\q1

Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline thine ear;
forget also thine own people, and thy father’s house; 
\q1

They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the
multitude of their riches; 
\q1

Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his
house is increased; 
\q1

Attend unto me, and hear me: I mourn in my complaint, and make a
noise; 
\q1

In God I will praise his word, in God I have put my trust;
I will not fear what flesh can do unto me. 
\q1

Gilead \add is\add* mine, and Manasseh \add is\add* mine; Ephraim also
\add is\add* the strength of mine head; Judah \add is\add* my lawgiver;
\q1

And all men shall fear, and shall declare the work of God;
for they shall wisely consider of his doing. 
\q1

\add He that is\add* our God \add is\add* the God of salvation;
and unto \nd GOD\nd* the Lord \add belong\add* the issues from death.
\q1

They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his
law; 
\q1

So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own
desire; 
\q1

So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent \add which\add*
he placed among men; 
\q1

Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven,
and behold, and visit this vine; 
\q1

Hear, O my people, and I will testify unto thee: O Israel,
if thou wilt hearken unto me; 
\q1

The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the
Hagarenes; 
\q1

Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants
of Tyre; 
\q1

As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains
on fire; 
\q1

Yea, the \nd LORD\nd* shall give \add that which is\add* good;
and our land shall yield her increase. 
\q1

Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants; \add how\add*
I do bear in my bosom \add the reproach of\add* all the mighty people;
\q1

Thou shalt not be afraid for the terror by night; \add nor\add*
for the arrow \add that\add* flieth by day; 
\q1

Because thou hast made the \nd LORD\nd*, \add which is\add*
my refuge, \add even\add* the most High, thy habitation; 
\q1

Blessed \add is\add* the man whom thou chastenest, O \nd LORD\nd*,
and teachest him out of thy law; 
\q1

For he hath looked down from the height of his sanctuary;
from heaven did the \nd LORD\nd* behold the earth; 
\q1

To declare the name of the \nd LORD\nd* in Zion, and his praise
in Jerusalem; 
\q1

Who redeemeth thy life from destruction; who crowneth thee with
lovingkindness and tender mercies; 
\q1

The \nd LORD\nd* hath prepared his throne in the heavens;
and his kingdom ruleth over all. 
\q1

He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle, and herb for the
service of man: that he may bring forth food out of the earth; 
\q1

The trees of the \nd LORD\nd* are full \add of sap;\add* the
cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted; 
\q1

Remember his marvellous works that he hath done; his wonders,
and the judgments of his mouth; 
\q1

Which \add covenant\add* he made with Abraham, and his oath
unto Isaac; 
\q1

When they went from one nation to another, from \add one\add*
kingdom to another people; 
\q1

And gave them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited
the labour of the people; 
\q1

Remember me, O \nd LORD\nd*, with the favour \add that thou bearest
unto\add* thy people: O visit me with thy salvation; 
\q1

They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things
in Egypt; 
\q1

Let the redeemed of the \nd LORD\nd* say \add so\add*, whom he hath
redeemed from the hand of the enemy; 
\q1

Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, \add being\add*
bound in affliction and iron; 
\q1

They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in
great waters; 
\q1

He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings
into dry ground; 
\q1

And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare
a city for habitation; 
\q1

He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly;
and suffereth not their cattle to decrease. 
\q1

Gilead \add is\add* mine; Manasseh \add is\add* mine; Ephraim also
\add is\add* the strength of mine head; Judah \add is\add* my lawgiver;
\q1

Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered with the \nd LORD\nd*;
and let not the sin of his mother be blotted out. 
\q1

He raiseth up the poor out of the dust, \add and\add* lifteth
the needy out of the dunghill; 
\q1

When Israel went out of Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people
of strange language; 
\q1

Tremble, thou earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence
of the God of Jacob; 
\q1

If \add it had not been\add* the \nd LORD\nd* who was on our side, now may
Israel say; 
\q1

Blessed \add is\add* every one that feareth the \nd LORD\nd*;
that walketh in his ways. 
\q1

How he sware unto the \nd LORD\nd*, \add and\add* vowed unto the
mighty \add God\add* of Jacob; 
\q1

Surely I will not come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go
up into my bed; 
\q1

They have mouths, but they speak not; eyes have they, but they
see not; 
\q1

To him that made great lights: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

And brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

To him which smote great kings: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

Sihon king of the Amorites: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

And Og the king of Bashan: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

And gave their land for an heritage: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

Who remembered us in our low estate: for his mercy \add endureth\add*
for ever: 
\q1

\add If\add* I take the wings of the morning, \add and\add*
dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea; 
\q1

They shall speak of the glory of thy kingdom, and talk of thy
power; 
\q1

Happy \add is he\add* that \add hath\add* the God of Jacob
for his help, whose hope \add is\add* in the \nd LORD\nd* his God:
\q1

To execute vengeance upon the heathen, \add and\add* punishments
upon the people; 
\q1

To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters
of iron; 
\q1
